:["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Aileen, James Patrick, Kieran.","Welsh (Pembrokeshire): habitational name from any of various minor places in Wales, in particular one near Pembroke with a major castle, named from Welsh <i>caer</i> ‘fort’ + <i>rhiw</i> ‘hill, slope’. The surname was taken to Ireland soon after the Norman invasion of England and was Gaelicized as <b>de Carrún</b>. In the 16th century a family called <i>Carew</i> from Devon played an important part in establishing the Tudor administration in Ireland.","Cornish (Somerset and Devon): from the cognate Cornish word <i>kerrow</i> (plural of <i>ker</i> ‘fort’), which occurs seven times as a placename in Cornwall."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"carew was born about 1297, in Ireland. She had at least 2 sons with Donal Caomh, \"the Handsome\", Mac Carthy Reagh, Prince of Carbery."},"et":{"about 1297–":"umbes 1297–Surnud","1295–1320":"1295–1320","1320–1366":"1320–1366","–Male":"Surnud","1297–Female":"1297–Surnud","ABT 1320":"umbes 1320","1366":"1366","1320":"1320","1297":"1297","1295":"1295","about 1297":"umbes 1297","Of Ireland":"Iirimaa","carbery":"Carbury, County Kildare, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"about 1297–":"noin 1297–Kuollut","1295–1320":"1295–1320","1320–1366":"1320–1366","–Male":"Kuollut","1297–Female":"1297–Kuollut","ABT 1320":"noin 1320","1366":"1366","1320":"1320","1297":"1297","1295":"1295","about 1297":"noin 1297","Of Ireland":"Irlanti","carbery":"Carbury, County Kildare, Irlanti"},"fr":{"about 1297–":"environ 1297–Décédée","1295–1320":"1295–1320","1320–1366":"1320–1366","–Male":"Décédé","1297–Female":"1297–Décédée","ABT 1320":"environ 1320","1366":"1366","1320":"1320","1297":"1297","1295":"1295","about 1297":"environ 1297","Of Ireland":"Irlande","carbery":"Carbury, County Kildare, Irlande","lifeSummary":"carew est née environ 1297, à Irlande. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils avec Donal Caomh, \"the Handsome\", Mac Carthy Reagh, Prince of Carbery."},"de":{"about 1297–":"um 1297–Verstorben","129